cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.RO 

This paper deals with the task of semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new method for weakly supervised semantic segmentation, which involves learning from limited annotations. This falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves natural language processing techniques for text-based annotations, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper deals with driving scenes, which involves robotics and autonomous systems, falling under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics).
